When you put `href="/fields/{{ hashid_encode($extrafield->id) }}"` in the `<a>` tag, the browser will redirect to the address. So, it will use the GET route. Probably the error is not in your ajax code, but in the `href` attribute.

TECHNOLOGY PROD NON PROD TOTAL

answer: Ah well, my bad for duplicating this incorrectly, though you were asking a quite similar question. The real answer is: you connect to a database, not a schema, so you don't pass it in a connection string. But: [`DataFrame.to_sql()`](http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/generated/pandas.DataFrame.to_sql.html) takes the "default" `schema` to use as a keyword argument, if the underlying DB supports schemas. Your database - schema analog is misleading. Schemas separate objects to namespaces *in a database*, and a user can access all objects in different schemas in a DB (given perms).

It isn't debug vs release. By default, you get -O2 -g, that is optimized but still with debug symbols. You can use make install-strip to remove the debug symbols. There is also make bootstrap-O3 to replace -O2 with -O3. This is all explained here: https://gcc.gnu.org/install/
